The formation of the passive voice is seldom given, since its omission can ocea- sion no embarrassment to one who is moderately acquainted with the paradigma of the Grammar. On the other hand, the oblique casea of noune and pronouna, and the perfect tenses of verbs, when peculial-ly irregular, are inserted in their alphabetical order, with a reference to the words from which they are derived. The derivation of worda, except when they immediately follow their primitives, is, in general, given in the vocabulary.
